bilingual.target: 约翰，你想要一些牛肉吗？

bilingual.source: OK, I'd like the beef noodles, please.

list.abstract: beef（英 [biːf]，美 [biːf]），英语单词，作名词时，为牛肉；牢骚；怨恨。作动词时，为抱怨；发牢骚。短语搭配有beef steak（牛排）。例句为“Their beef steak is good, too.（他们的牛排也不错。）” beef相关近义词有muscle、hotpot等。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, beef, I'm going to miss you so much.
yingyinNormal.zh: 牛肉，我会很想念你的。

yingyinNormal.en: OK, so mushrooms out, and onto the beef, like that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，将蘑菇放在牛肉上，就像这样。

yingyinNormal.en: Here's two dollars. Go buy some beef jerky. I don't want beef jerky.
yingyinNormal.zh: 给你两块钱，去买点牛肉干。我不想吃牛肉干。

yingyinNormal.en: Now to cook the marinated beef. Wok on, oil in. Wok is ready. It's smoking. In with the beef.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在炒腌好的牛肉。放上锅，倒些油，锅热了，冒烟了，放入牛肉。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, when you put the beef in, just make sure it has time to just settle a little bit before you start to stir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 放入牛肉后，要保证牛肉在锅底煎一小会，然后再开始翻炒。

yingyinNormal.en: So that's the beef done. Out on top of the spinach, like so.
yingyinNormal.zh: 牛肉做好了，盛在菠菜上，就像这样。

yingyinNormal.en: Now the beef is done. I'm going to put it to one side, let it rest.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在牛肉做好了，我把它放在一边，静置一会。

yingyinNormal.en: I just ordered a case of Dinty Moore beef stew and two live lobsters on Amazon.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我刚在亚马逊上订了一箱炖牛肉罐头和两只活龙虾。

yingyinNormal.en: So there's my version of beef in oyster sauce, essentially, three stir-frys in one dish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就是我做的蚝油牛肉，其实就是三菜合一。

yingyinNormal.en: If there's a single food that symbolizes the American diet for me, it's beef.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果有一种食物能作为美国食品的标志，非牛肉莫属。

yingyinNormal.en: In with the beef and let that sizzle. Brown it on one side and then brown the other side.
yingyinNormal.zh: 放入牛肉，就会发出滋滋声。分别将两面煎成棕色。

yingyinNormal.en: What did they give you? Turkey and roast beef with Swiss and lettuce on whole wheat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那他们给你的什么？火鸡和烤牛肉全麦上放的芝士和生菜。

yingyinNormal.en: Gorgeous bit of the beef there. Some of these delicious smoky mushrooms. Bit of salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先是香喷喷的牛肉，然后加入热气腾腾的蘑菇，配一些莴苣。

yingyinNormal.en: This vast quantity of corn makes it possible to produce beef on an industrial scale.
yingyinNormal.zh: 巨量的玉米让这一切成为可能，让我们能够以工业级的规模生产牛肉。

yingyinNormal.en: Sue's given us a list of hot pot ingredients to find in the market, lotus root, mushrooms and beef.
yingyinNormal.zh: 苏给了我们一张火锅料单到市场入货，莲藕，蘑菇还有牛肉。

yingyinNormal.en: The beef? Yeah, that was weird to me, too. But then, you know, I thought "well, there's mincemeat pie."
yingyinNormal.zh: 炒牛肉吗？我也觉得有点奇怪，不过我想连甜肉馅饼都有了。

yingyinNormal.en: What you got over there? Tacos? No. No. They're just ground beef smileys. Those are tacos.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是什么？墨西哥卷饼吗？不，它们只是牛肉包大饼。那是墨西哥卷饼。

yingyinNormal.en: Before the beef comes out, I'm going to add a pinch or two of dried chilli flakes, and these give a gorgeous kick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在牛肉出锅前，挑一点干辣椒末放进去，使肉鲜香中带些麻辣。

yingyinNormal.en: I've always been a little confused about this. Why don't hindus eat beef? We believe cows are gods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我一直对这事儿有些疑惑，为什么印度教不准吃牛肉？我们相信牛就是神。

yingyinNormal.en: So, I'm going to show you one of my favorites, Sichuan orange beef, and it's really authentic in flavor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以，我要来展示一下我最拿手的四川香橙牛肉，这真的是地道的川味。

sense_info_list.en: meat that comes from a cow

examination_example.sentence: If the sustainable-egg rollout is successful, it could open the floodgates for regenerative <highlight>beef</highlight>, broccoli, and beyond.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果可持续鸡蛋推广成功，它可能会为再生牛肉、西兰花等打开闸门。

examination_example.sentence: Doubtless a piece of boiled <highlight>beef</highlight> can always be served up on Sunday alongside some steamed vegetables, without the Yorkshire pudding and no wine.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 毫无疑问，在周日，一块煮牛肉总是可以和一些蒸蔬菜一起上桌，没有约克郡布丁，也没有葡萄酒。

examination_example.sentence: If you plan properly, you'll know that you only need 350g of shin of <highlight>beef</highlight> not whatever weight is pre-packed in the supermarket chiller.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你计划得当，你会知道你只需要350克的牛胫骨，而不是超市冰箱中预装的任何重量。

examination_example.sentence: Yet as distrust has risen toward all media, people may be starting to <highlight>beef</highlight> up their media literacy skills.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，随着对所有媒体的不信任上升，人们可能开始加强他们的媒体素养技能。

sense_info_list.en: a steer, cow, or bull especially when fattened for food
